        "description": "<p>Similar to <a href=\"https://www.mobygames.com/game/30917/phase/\">Phase</a>, <em>musika</em> is a game that taps into the user's music library to create the gameplay. The core concept is interactive music visualization with the addition of gameplay elements. Before starting, a selection of music on the iPod is made based on playlists, individual songs, genres or artists, along with three difficulty levels: Casual, Active and Intense.</p>\n<p>While the song is playing, letters appear on the screen based on a wide range of distorted effects. When a character flashes up that is part of the song title, players need to press the centre button to confirm. Based on the speed and accuracy, a score is rewarded. When the character is not part of the title, the skip forward/back buttons need to be pressed. Make a mistake (letting a character pass or a mistake), and blocks are added to the song title shown at the bottom of the screen, which need to be removed again.</p>\n<p>When every character has been hit five times, the songs ends. Getting multiple correct character in a row leads to score multipliers and there are bonuses such as almighty (shield that protects against misses, passes and blocks), de-block (remove all blocks), double clear points (2x multiplier) and double score. Album art is shown in the bottom left corner of the screen and the level progress in the top right. Players can tweak the visual effects and add a custom message shown during gameplay. The game created in conjunction with Sony BMG.</p>",
